name: Henrik Kjellberg
custom Notes: As President, Henrik Kjellberg oversees all aspects of the Hotwire Group's two brands: Hotwire® and CarRentals.com™.  Henrik joined Hotwire in 2013, but started his career with the Expedia Inc. family in 2001, launching Expedia-branded websites in Italy and Holland. Prior to Hotwire, he was president of Expedia Affiliate Network (EAN) worldwide, Expedia's business-to-business division, providing large and small-scale affiliates with Expedia's state of the art booking and marketing solutions.  Henrik also acted as president of Expedia Asia Pacific, launching Expedia's regional marketing office in Hong Kong where he was responsible for the Expedia and hotels.com® brands in APAC as well as China's eLong, a leading Chinese online travel company. Henrik continues to act as Chairman of eLong.  Before joining Expedia, Henrik launched the e-commerce division for Spray, a leading Swedish Internet portal. Henrik started his career with Procter & Gamble Nordic in the sales and marketing division.  Henrik holds a Master of Science in Economics from the Stockholm School of Economics.
